WEBVTT

01:48.692 --> 01:49.984
Stop him!

01:53.029 --> 01:54.989
Damn it!

01:56.074 --> 01:57.283
Get her back!

01:58.326 --> 02:01.538
They're getting away!
Stop him!

02:02.580 --> 02:03.873
Go around!

02:15.510 --> 02:17.846
There they are!

02:22.475 --> 02:25.562
Stop right there!

03:34.172 --> 03:34.755
Stand back!

03:34.756 --> 03:37.591
Yoshimitsu-sama...

03:37.592 --> 03:38.592
I accept my defeat.

03:39.636 --> 03:41.304
This is my destiny.

03:42.555 --> 03:46.226
I accept my defeat.

03:46.893 --> 03:48.769
I accept my destiny.

03:48.770 --> 03:53.608
Please understand that.

04:02.158 --> 04:04.577
Hold it!

04:09.874 --> 04:11.751
Yoshimitsu-sama!

05:30.705 --> 05:34.917
Look.
There's a cave down there.

05:34.918 --> 05:39.296
Maybe it was formed
by the river stream.

05:39.297 --> 05:41.758
Hmm.

06:08.242 --> 06:12.829
Wow. Look at this.

06:12.830 --> 06:17.793
I wonder how long this cave
has been around.

06:17.794 --> 06:20.463
Hmm.

06:21.631 --> 06:25.092
Geez. It's kind of spooky.

06:25.093 --> 06:28.805
It's fine.

06:47.615 --> 06:52.615
It's cold in here.
I don't want to go any further.

06:53.246 --> 06:56.916
Then, you stay here.

07:11.264 --> 07:14.017
I'll go check a little bit deeper.

07:51.387 --> 07:54.097
<i>I first heard about it on the news.</i>

07:54.098 --> 07:55.390
<i>A few scattered reports</i>

07:55.391 --> 07:59.603
<i>of a 400-year-old body
found frozen in the ice.</i>

07:59.604 --> 08:02.689
<i>It was the kind of story
that sparks the imagination,</i>

08:02.690 --> 08:05.317
<i>gives newscasters
something to joke about,</i>

08:05.318 --> 08:07.111
<i>and then fades into oblivion.</i>

08:12.366 --> 08:15.077
<i>For me, it was a job opportunity.</i>

08:15.078 --> 08:18.956
<i>And, at first, this looked
like just another assignment...</i>

08:40.227 --> 08:43.230
Excuse me, I have an appointment
with Dr. Richards.

08:43.231 --> 08:46.191
- I'm Alan Richards.
- Hi. I'm Chris Welles.

08:46.192 --> 08:47.985
Yes, I know.

08:49.320 --> 08:50.822
Thank you.

08:51.906 --> 08:55.743
How do you do?
Let's get to work, shall we?

09:02.750 --> 09:04.501
You know what this is about?

09:04.502 --> 09:06.337
President Shogun?

09:08.047 --> 09:09.966
What else have you heard?

09:11.050 --> 09:13.469
They found this man frozen in ice,
chipped him out,

09:13.636 --> 09:16.304
and sent him to you for an autopsy.

09:16.305 --> 09:19.891
Well, it's more than that.

09:19.892 --> 09:21.686
Much more.

09:26.232 --> 09:30.068
<i>My field is Oriental History,
and they questioned me closely,</i>

09:30.069 --> 09:33.363
<i>trying to determine
the limits of my experience.</i>

09:33.364 --> 09:36.449
<i>My weak point was that
I could speak little Japanese.</i>

09:36.450 --> 09:38.494
<i>But they let that pass.</i>

09:38.661 --> 09:41.788
<i>Something more important
was on their minds.</i>

09:41.789 --> 09:44.708
<i>They weren't going to
perform an autopsy.</i>

09:44.709 --> 09:48.754
<i>They were going to bring that man
back to life.</i>

09:55.011 --> 09:58.096
- Body fluids, stable.
- Good.

09:58.097 --> 10:00.933
Dr. Richards, double-check please.

10:02.101 --> 10:03.686
Very good, Ellie.

10:07.440 --> 10:09.525
Carl, do you have a reading
on cerebral stats?

10:10.359 --> 10:12.402
35.9... 36.

10:12.403 --> 10:15.447
7.5 minutes to stabilized brain temperature

10:15.448 --> 10:18.033
before neuro-disintegration.

10:18.034 --> 10:19.660
Carl, brainwave stats.

10:20.411 --> 10:23.915
Brainwave monitor
functioning is steady at zero.

10:25.541 --> 10:27.167
Very well.
What's your body core temperature?

10:27.168 --> 10:32.168
Fahrenheit 98.4, .5, .6...

10:32.506 --> 10:33.506
We have critical.

10:35.509 --> 10:37.428
Engage thermal capacitor, now.

10:44.393 --> 10:47.563
One thing, if this goes wrong,
anybody finds out about it...

10:47.730 --> 10:48.897
I hear you.

11:12.088 --> 11:14.090
Scalpel.

11:17.510 --> 11:19.345
Let's do it.

11:32.858 --> 11:35.110
Suction.

11:35.111 --> 11:37.738
Cerebral and core, steady at 36.

11:42.618 --> 11:45.246
Cardiac stimulant, mark?

11:46.414 --> 11:48.206
90 seconds, mark.

11:48.207 --> 11:51.126
Respirator on... now.

11:55.172 --> 11:58.341
Okay, Carl, let's hook him up.

11:58.342 --> 12:01.220
Stand by for bypass.

12:15.318 --> 12:19.237
Pumping.
Ready for electro-shock.

12:19.238 --> 12:21.990
- Sixty seconds.
- Okay. Stand by.

12:21.991 --> 12:23.659
Fifty-five seconds...

12:23.826 --> 12:26.287
- Clear.
- Hit it.

12:33.169 --> 12:35.628
Nothing. What's the count?

12:35.629 --> 12:39.550
- Forty seconds.
- Clear.

12:40.509 --> 12:42.469
Go.

12:42.470 --> 12:47.470
Thirty seconds.

12:47.600 --> 12:50.644
- We're running out of time, Alan.
- I know, I know.

12:50.811 --> 12:53.521
Come on, let's do it!
Let's go! Up the volt!

12:53.522 --> 12:56.150
- Clear.
- Again.

13:04.367 --> 13:06.534
Flush him out, Ellie.

13:06.535 --> 13:08.162
Twenty.

13:09.121 --> 13:10.872
Hit it, Pete.

13:10.873 --> 13:13.208
- Ten seconds.
- Goddamn it, hit it, Pete!

13:13.209 --> 13:15.377
Wait. Listen.

13:32.728 --> 13:36.272
- We did it.
- We did it! We have brain activity!

13:36.273 --> 13:39.235
Beautiful. That's beautiful.

14:13.436 --> 14:14.728
<i>Weeks passed,</i>

14:14.895 --> 14:18.731
<i>and the samurai's condition
continued to improve.</i>

14:18.732 --> 14:22.402
<i>I went about my research
as discreetly as possible,</i>

14:22.403 --> 14:25.405
<i>for Alan had ordered
complete secrecy.</i>

14:25.406 --> 14:29.451
<i>The Institute and his career
were on the line.</i>

14:38.794 --> 14:41.754
This is something special.

14:41.755 --> 14:44.758
It suggests a real master.

14:44.925 --> 14:46.676
It looks sharp.

14:46.677 --> 14:49.304
The old katana had the sharpest,

14:49.305 --> 14:51.764
hardest, best-tempered blades
in the world.

14:51.765 --> 14:55.728
They were the soul of the samurai.

14:56.353 --> 14:58.772
The great swords...

14:58.939 --> 15:02.442
And this is a great one...

15:02.443 --> 15:05.653
Were thought to have
a life of their own.

15:05.654 --> 15:08.782
A spirit,
the embodiment of bushido.

15:08.949 --> 15:11.242
- The Way of the Warrior.
- Yes.

15:11.243 --> 15:14.496
A samurai spent his entire life
preparing for death.

15:14.497 --> 15:20.669
So at the critical moment,
he could face it without hesitation.

15:22.046 --> 15:26.175
And the autopsy?
How is it going?

15:27.176 --> 15:29.595
I'm not supposed to discuss it.

15:33.349 --> 15:35.433
I'll be in touch.

15:35.434 --> 15:37.435
I look forward to it.

15:37.436 --> 15:38.646
Thank you, Professor.

15:39.813 --> 15:41.774
Bye-bye.

15:55.579 --> 15:57.288
Hi, stranger.
What do you got for me?

15:57.289 --> 16:01.042
Not much so far,
but I did some research on the sword.

16:01.043 --> 16:02.878
These are a real find, Alan.

16:03.045 --> 16:07.174
They're made by Kunimitsu,
one of the greatest swordsmiths ever.

16:09.176 --> 16:10.886
These are the best of the best.

16:11.053 --> 16:12.720
They're worth a fortune
on the open market.

16:12.721 --> 16:15.098
Great.

16:15.099 --> 16:19.227
He was a first-rate samurai, a master.

16:19.228 --> 16:23.148
Well, I wonder
what he's going to think of us.

17:00.394 --> 17:02.605
Oh...

18:22.559 --> 18:25.645
Oh, my God. Oh, my...

18:25.646 --> 18:27.438
Stay there.

18:27.439 --> 18:31.485
Don't move!
Just stay right there!

18:32.277 --> 18:34.113
Stay right there.

18:38.200 --> 18:39.867
Dr. Richards!

18:39.868 --> 18:41.870
Dr. Richards!

18:46.792 --> 18:49.461
Fantastic.

18:58.637 --> 19:01.056
Incredible.

19:09.189 --> 19:12.443
This is truly incredible.

19:26.790 --> 19:30.753
- What's he saying?
- I can't make it out.

19:46.310 --> 19:48.853
Yoshi... something.

19:48.854 --> 19:52.024
- That must be his name.
- Yoshi.

19:56.862 --> 19:59.447
We took his swords.
We shouldn't have done that.

19:59.448 --> 20:02.743
No one's going to hurt him.
Tell him that.

20:05.913 --> 20:07.790
No one's going to hurt you.

20:14.588 --> 20:15.838
Look at him.

20:15.839 --> 20:18.050
We've got to show him
that this isn't a nightmare,

20:18.258 --> 20:21.053
that he's not crazy.

20:21.261 --> 20:24.096
- Can I get his things?
- You want to return his swords?

20:24.097 --> 20:25.640
We have to.

20:25.641 --> 20:27.558
It's his only link
to the world he knows.

20:27.559 --> 20:28.601
So?

20:28.602 --> 20:31.103
So, if we don't,
he'll think he's a prisoner.

20:31.104 --> 20:34.900
A samurai would prefer death.

21:32.499 --> 21:35.002
Be ready for anything.

22:06.533 --> 22:09.453
Let's leave him for now.

22:48.617 --> 22:50.243
Hi.

22:53.372 --> 22:55.164
<i>Day after day,</i>

22:55.165 --> 22:58.042
<i>I surrounded him
with things from his past.</i>

22:58.043 --> 23:00.628
<i>And day after day, I studied him,</i>

23:00.629 --> 23:05.549
<i>hoping for a sign of trust,
of recognition...</i>

23:05.550 --> 23:07.260
<i>of anything.</i>

23:19.606 --> 23:22.234
Go on.

23:29.449 --> 23:30.826
Sake.

24:01.148 --> 24:02.733
Sake.

24:04.317 --> 24:07.237
Those swords, what are they worth?

24:09.656 --> 24:12.117
No, really, how much?

24:13.118 --> 24:16.038
More than most people
make in a lifetime.

24:19.791 --> 24:21.209
How's the patient?

24:27.382 --> 24:29.384
Why does he do that?

24:29.551 --> 24:31.594
Maybe he doesn't like you.

24:31.595 --> 24:35.097
No, I'm serious.
I'm worried about brain damage.

24:35.098 --> 24:37.684
He doesn't respond very well.

25:04.961 --> 25:06.296
Now, you.

25:28.401 --> 25:30.654
No, it doesn't work like that.

26:41.349 --> 26:44.811
Okay, Charlie, I want the swords!

27:37.948 --> 27:40.158
Jonathan...

27:40.867 --> 27:42.827
<i>Jonathan Martin...</i>

27:56.841 --> 27:59.886
<i>No one dresses
a woman like Jonathan Martin.</i>

